Minister for Communication and Information Technology Dr Faustine Ndugulile ordered Tanzania Communication Regulatory Authority (TCRA) to lower charges of online TV registration and licensing as part of promoting creativity and empowering the youth. Speaking in Arusha, Â the Minister directed the regulatory authority to review the ban it imposed on registration and licensing of fresh online television, insisting June is way too far. "I need this to be resolved in exactly one month," he said. Dr Ndugulile threatened to take stern legal measures against mobile phone repairs found guilty of erasing IMEI numbers of their customers' phones.